node.text:
Proper core and pelvic core control is not just for my baby mamas :) This proper activation and breathing technique is something everyone should be able to do. 

A diastasis recti can happen to anyone, not just pregnant woman. I have treated male patients for this issue as well! You can also see this midline bulge with people who are unable to regulate their core properly during certain exercises. So being able to control that outward pressure that causes your belly to bulge is an important skill to have for everyone!

Some benefits of these exercises techniques:
👉🏼prevention and treatment of a diastasis recti
👉🏼prevention and treatment of urinary incontinence or other pelvic floor related issues
👉🏼help regulate intra-abdominal pressure and overall core control
👉🏼appropriate for pre/postnatal women

This is what you see me doing in my workout videos. Being able to breathe through exercises and engage properly will continue to be super important as I go though my pregnancy! 

#daretobeactiveprepostnatal

node.text:
So I don’t talk about personal things very often, but I wouldn’t feel right starting to post again about exercise and pregnancy without sharing my journey thus far. It has been a long tough road, and I know hearing other women’s stories helped me. So maybe sharing a little bit of mine could help someone else. 

I should note that I got in a bad habit of calling Hyperemesis gravidarum the wrong thing and I kept doing it in this video 🤦🏻‍♀️ So apologies for that.

To all the women who went through or are going through HG or fertility problems...I feel you. You are a badass. You got this. 

#hyperemisisgravidarum #infertility

node.title: Pregnancy Journey + my experience with HG

node.text:
Everyone needs to be training their rotator cuff muscles. Why? Watch the video to learn. 

These muscles are dynamic stabilizers, so aim for high repetition with low weight. Three sets to failure is a good place to start. Failure means you are unable to compete the full range of motion or you lose correct form.

More exercises to follow!

#daretobeactiveshoulders
#daretobeactiveupperbody 
#daretobeactive

node.text:
— Breakfast bagels for 2 —

🥯sesame bagels
🍳eggs (love these egg molds from @williamssonoma)
🧀 applewood smoked cheddar cheese
🦃 turkey meat
🥑avo mayo
🥒cucumber

one of my favorite meals!

👉🏼Did this workout from the DTBA app with some third trimester modifications: 

- goblet squat instead of pop squat 
- single arm shoulder press instead of back lunge with iso overhead press
- plank pull through from knees 
- side plank rotation from knees

Been loving doing these workouts throughout my pregnancy! Try it out for free for 7 days at the link in my bio 👍🏼

💥Here are more stretches I have been consistently doing throughout this pregnancy. Lots of focus on thoracic and lumbar mobility, especially rotation and side bend. Those two movements have felt the most limited!

#daretobeactive
#daretobeactiveprepostnatal

node.text:
🤰🏻Continuing to work on my hip and lower body strength and mobility in these last couple weeks. Modifying by taking longer breaks between sets, and having a wider stance to make room for belly. 

🌬Remember to always connect your breathing and core and pelvic floor engagement to the exercise (check out how to do this on my IGTV)

4x10 👇🏼
1. deadlift 
2. RDL
3. heel elevated goblet squat

30x 👇🏼 
1. single leg bridge 
2. bridge + pulse 
3. side plank abduction 
4. floating clamshell 
5. hip internal rotation 

- Pregnant woman should always consult with their health care provider about whether or how to adjust their physical activity during pregnancy and postpartum. 

#daretobeactive
#daretobeactivelowerbody
#daretobeactiveprepostnatal
